{"name": "chasing-targets-gym", "metadata": {"name": "chasing-targets-gym", "version": "0.0.9", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 2 - Pre-Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT License  Copyright (c) 2023 Bryce Ferenczi  Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of this software and associated documentation files (the \"Software\"), to deal in the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell copies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is furnished to do so, subject to the following conditions:  The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all copies or substantial portions of the Software.  THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy", "gymnasium", "pygame"], "summary": "Simple gym environment for multiple agents to chase multiple (dumb) targets", "upload_time": 1734443217}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  codestyle: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg\n    :target: https://github.com/psf/black\n    ```\n  license: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/chasing-targets-gym\n    :alt: PyPI - License\n    :target: https://github.com/5had3z/chasing-targets-gym/blob/main/LICENSE\n    ```\n  python: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/chasing-targets-gym\n    :alt: PyPI - Python Version\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/chasing-targets-gym/\n    ```\n  version: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/chasing-targets-gym\n    :alt: PyPI - Package Version\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/chasing-targets-gym/\n    ```\n---\n\n# Chasing Targets Gym\n\n{{ version }} {{ python }} {{ license }} {{ codestyle }}\n\n## Introduction\n\nThis is a simple gym environment that sets up a set of robots and targets for them to chase.\nThese targets are dumb, they simply move at a constant speed and bounce off the \"limits\" of\nthe simulation environment. The intention is that the robots will chase after these targets,\nand switch to a new target after catching their current one. The targets are \"transparent\" and\nrobots are free to ignore \"avoiding them\", the intention is that they avoid each other. An\nexample of a simulation with robot controller is shown below.\n\n```{image} misc/example_sim.gif\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nSince this uses the gymnasium, you can spin an environment up same as any other env, and you can use our optimized planner. A script is included that shows of this planner and environment when you install this library `` `chasing-targets-example --max-step=500` ``.\n\n```python\nfrom gymnasium import Env, make\nfrom chasing_targets_gym.planner import Planner\n\nenv: Env = make(\n    \"ChasingTargets-v0\",\n    render_mode=\"human\",\n    n_robots=10,\n    n_targets=3,\n    robot_radius=0.1,\n    max_velocity=0.5,\n    target_velocity_std=0.5,\n    max_episode_steps=1000,\n)\n\nplanner = Planner(\n    env.get_wrapper_attr(\"robot_radius\"),\n    env.get_wrapper_attr(\"dt\"),\n    env.get_wrapper_attr(\"max_velocity\"),\n)\n```\n\n## Installation\n\nEither you can clone and pip install the source, or you can install via pypi.\nIf installing from source seems to stall for no apparent reason, try --no-build-isolation.\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/5had3z/chasing-targets-gym && cd chasing-targets-gym && pip3 install -e .\n```\n\nOtherwise install pypi package\n\n```bash\npip3 install chasing-targets-gym\n```\n\n## Some Credit\n\nI was pointed to a basic environment [here](https://github.com/riiswa/planning-multi-robot-gym) but it didn't\nreally match what I wanted, so I made my own based off this.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "chasing_targets_gym.run", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python3"], "functions": [{"name": "chasing_targets_gym.run.update_step", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "robots", "type": {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "target_pos", "type": {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Returns action for robot using pure pursuit algorithm"]}, {"name": "chasing_targets_gym.run.pure_pursuit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obs", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.ndarray", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "np.ndarray", "xref": {"fqname": "nump